# Copy to .npmrc and set your Ping Identity / org registry for @pingux scope.
# Required to install @pingux/astro (depends on @pingux/onyx-tokens, not on public npm).
#
# Quick start:
#   1. cp .npmrc.example .npmrc
#   2. Edit .npmrc: set @pingux:registry= to your org's registry URL (get from Ping Identity or internal docs; may be VPN-only).
#   3. If the registry requires auth, add a line: //your-registry-host/:_authToken=${NPM_TOKEN}
#   4. pnpm install
#
# Example (replace with your registry URL and auth if needed):
# @pingux:registry=https://npm.pingidentity.com/
# //npm.pingidentity.com/:_authToken=${NPM_TOKEN}
#
# After configuring, run: pnpm install
# See docs/ASTRO_MIGRATION_PLAN.md for full migration steps.
